name: Sulawesi Organic Gunung Karua Farm
notes: Earth-toned sweetness and woodsy character like fresh forest greenery, rice syrup, dried apple, woody spice, tobacco and a peat note that hints at aged Scotch in the nose. City+ to Full City+.

name: Guatemala Acatenango Gesha Lot 2
notes: A competition-level and incredibly floral Gesha coffee, notes of star jasmine, lilac, bergamot citrus, orange blossom, Earl Grey and corn silk teas, spiced cider and a candied sweetness underneath it all. City to City+

name: Kenya Nyeri Gachatha AB
notes: Light roasts have flavors of pulpy orange, dried currant, piquant black tea and lemon rind while Full City produces more of a berry-toned, chocolatey cup profile with accents of grape jelly. City to Full City.

name: Papua New Guinea Baroida Estate
notes: A sweet, earth-toned coffee with herbal honey sweetness, accents of basil and fresh tarragon, a saturated green tea flavor, rustic palm and date sugars, tart citrus, and sandalwood aroma. City+.

name: Yuni Na Aw Anaerobic Washed
notes: Our washed coffee from Na Aw is a clean, consistent, balanced, and mild coffee with a tea-like character that expresses itself with hints of citrus, vanilla, and herbal undertones.

name: Yuni Xam Tai Natural Yeast Process
notes: This fruit forward complex coffee blends a deep red wine-like ferment with a surprisingly bright citrus acidity and notes of strawberry and tamarind.

name: Yuni Xam Tai Anaerobic Washed Process
notes: Our Xam Tai washed coffee consists of a mix of Catimor, Java, and Yellow Caturra varieties, and brings a deep syrupy complexity to the cup with lemon like acidity and hints of vanilla, cocoa powder and papaya. This versatile coffee can hold up as a single origin drip or espresso and can complement other coffees in a blend as well.

name: Ethiopia Dry Process Dari Kidame
notes: Fruits are well-integrated into the coffee's sweetness, and acidity is bright for dry process. Date sugar, orange marmalade, mango, and aromatic cedar. Intense chocolate and a blueberry hint in dark roasts. City to Full City.

name: Ethiopia Dry Process Hambela Dabaye
notes: City and City+ roasts make a very nice pour over, fruit is obvious but not overpowering, strawberry jam, nectarine, and berry-like brightness connect to floral aromatics that touch on jasmine, and ripe fruits. City to Full City.

name: Rwanda Karongi Gitesi
notes: A nice base sweetness of sugar cane juice, spiced Darjeeling tea aroma, light fruited hints, lemon citrus accent and acidic impression. Elegant pour over and spiced chocolate as espresso. City to Full City. Good for espresso.

name: Papua New Guinea Kimel AA
notes: Brews up a balanced cup, honey sweetness leads into accents of green tea, rindy orange, roasted barley, sarsaparilla, and saffron. Dark chocolate bittersweetness when roasted dark. City+ to Full City+.

name: Ethiopia Dry Process Bombe Basha
notes: Bombe Basha is a fruit forward dry process coffee accented by perfumed floral hints, flavors of juicy blueberry, concord grape, plum, passion fruit tropicals, and a malty note that comes off like peach infused beer. City to City+.

name: Ethiopia Guji Hambela Dabaye
notes: Lighter  roasts produce a layered sweetness of partially refined sugars, fruited accents of limeade, lychee fruit, orange jello, a little golden plum, and a floral jasmine aroma crowns the cup. City to City+.

name: Colombia Honey Process Libardo Gómez
notes: Cup flavors encapsulate juicy sweetness, flavors of pressed pear and cherry juices, notes of tart golden plum, fresh fig, and produces a moderate level of acidity that threads the complex cup flavors together. City to City+.

name: Sumatra Ribang Gayo
notes: Intense sweetenss of palm sugar and dark fruits, muscat grape, fermented blackberry, sweet tobacco, aromatic cedar, and waves of bittersweetness when roasted dark. City to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Brazil Adair Oliveira Neto
notes: Atypical Brazil dry process, pleasant flavors of simple brown sugars are propped up by mild apple-like acidity, a crisp Bartlett pear note, and subtle sweet herbals add an aromatic quality to the cup. City to Full City.

name: Nicaragua Los Altiplanos Java
notes: Mild Java cultivar characteristics, herbal aromatics, moderate supporting sweetness and acidity, and accents of Malta barley soda, buckwheat tea, lemon zest, woody cinnamon stick, and soft bittersweetness. City+ to Full City.

name: Ethiopia Organic Geta Bore Coop
notes: Dynamic cup flavors, syrupy sweetness, stone fruit, peach tea, mango yogurt, and cardamom spice. A very friendly dark roast candidate too, not too bittersweet, with a moderate sense of fruit. City to Full City+. Good Ethiopian espresso.

name: Ethiopia Dry Process Buno Dambi Uddo
notes: A berry-centered coffee with flavorful fruits, dry process Dambi Uddo pulls out an array of top notes like plump blueberry, blackberry and cranberry juice, fruit leather, winey accents, and chocolate-covered raisins. City to Full City.

name: Yemen Mokha Peaberry
notes: Middle roasts show nice roast intensity, interspersed with hints of pumpkin bread, hazelnut chocolate, sesame cookie, tobacco, whole spices, burnt marshmallow, and aromatic wood. City+ to Full City+. Good for espresso.

name: Ethiopia Yirga Cheffe Halo Beriti
notes: 'Floral' tops my list of aromatic descriptors, along with pronounced cane sugar sweetness that leads to a sweet finish, notes of fresh gardenia and freesia flowers, pink gum, berry taffy, and an herbal rue accent. City to City+.

name: Colombia Huila Sidra Cultivar
notes: Intense cup sweetness is illuminated by a fruited brightness that gives the coffee a crisp, citric backbone. Juicy accents of plum, white grape, a hint of orange drink, and lasting sweetness through to the finish. City to Full City.

name: Ethiopia Dogo Sodu
notes: Aromatic flavors push this natural to another level, fruit salad, red raspberry, strawberry, honeydew melon, mango, papaya, rue herb, fruit-florals, baking spice, and a hint of Earl Grey tea. City to Full City.

name: Nicaragua Dipilto San Salvador Java
notes: Zesty lemon peel informs acidity, with barley malt syrup and caramel sweetness, hints of black tea, herbal bitters, earthy yellow tea, wood-spice aroma, and bittering cocoa. City+ to Full City.

name: Kenya Nyeri Gichathaini AB
notes: Stunning flavor profiles of bright fruits and aromatic spices that lead to a long, contemplative finish. Notes of lemony citrus, orange spice tea, mulled cranberry juice, and Earl Grey. City to Full City.

name: Ethiopia Dry Process Korate
notes: Korate is a delight to sip and enjoy the shifting flavor profiles as it cools. A clean dry process that's bright and floral, with notes of white honey, apricot, mango, berry tea, passion fruit, and aromatic jasmine. City to Full City.
